line_1: And steeps in tears the robe to which she clings!
line_2: See, to his aid his child, soft ZILIA, springs,

line_1: From the dwarf Daisy, which, like infants, clings,
line_2: And fears to leave the earth from whence it springs,

line_1: When her lov'd infant to her bosom clings,
line_2: When round her neck his eager arms he flings,

line_1: Perch'd on her crest the Griffin Discord clings,
line_2: And Giant Murder rides between her wings;

line_1: Round each fair Nymph her dropping mantle clings,
line_2: And Loves emerging shake their showery wings.
